To create a "flat" CTAN package:

  cd to inter, the directory containing the texmf tree
  mkdir doc enc map latex opentype type1 tfm vf
  cd doc
  ln -s ../texmf/doc/fonts/inter/* .
  rm README  (because it would duplicate the top-level README)
  cd ../enc
  ln -s ../texmf/fonts/enc/dvips/inter/* .
  cd ../map
  ln -s ../texmf/fonts/map/dvips/inter/* .
  cd ../latex
  ln -s ../texmf/tex/latex/inter/* .
  cd ../opentype
  ln -s ../texmf/fonts/opentype/public/inter/* .
  cd ../type1
  ln -s ../texmf/fonts/type1/public/inter/* .
  cd ../tfm
  ln -s ../texmf/fonts/tfm/public/inter/* .
  cd ../vf
  ln -s ../texmf/fonts/vf/public/inter/* .
  mv texmf/inter.tds.zip ..
  cd ../..
  zip -r inter.zip inter/README inter.tds.zip inter/doc inter/enc inter/map inter/latex inter/opentype inter/type1 inter/tfm inter/vf

Now inter.zip can be uploaded to CTAN.

  
